<br>
&quot;I'm sure anyone, including I could've done that!&quot;<br>
<br>
Just as Yakut caused the fire the circle around Amarice and her bedroll, she began to gently grasp at the hilt of her sword.  Then she thought to herself, 'What the hell could I do with my sword to a flame?  Fan it away?'  then she quickly let it go before Yakut noticed so she couldn't make fun of her.  Everytime Amarice figured she was being threatened she would grab hold of her sword.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ohhh, that was as stupid as a card trick.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Of course Amarice was lying, the flame truely did slightly scare her.  But she would never admit if something upsetted her, even if someone was threatning her emotionally.  She did not want anyone seeing her weaknesses. <p>Ø×××|¯A_m¯a_r¯i_c¯e_&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#0000FF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amazonqueenyakut>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen of Tanis River Valley</span><br>  Posts: 243<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/1/02 11:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.hometown.aol.com/amznqyakut1/images/yakut3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I can read ya like a book child</span><hr size=1> Yakut smirked and shook her head. Young ones, I swear.<br>
<br>
&quot;You can't fool someone who practices the Craft of the Wise. My magick is anything but a card trick, child. I know things even the wisest of Kings and Queens would shudder at...It's the price you pay as a Shaman of the Olden Ways.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yakut laid down on her bedroll and starred up into the sky..it was getting dark out. Star began peeking from the blanketing sky.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh child, many things will come to you, but patience is a virtue. Never seek, just find. Be found. When you are one with something, you do not control, you listen with your mind.&quot;<br>
<br>
